Suppose that $f : RR -> RR$ is infinitely differentiable and
satisfies both of the following properties:

#set enum(numbering: "(a)")

+ $f(1) = 2$,
+ If $alpha, beta$ are real numbers satisfying $alpha^2 + beta^2 = 1$,
  then $f(alpha x) f(beta x) = f(x)$ for all $x$.

Find $f(x)$. Guesswork will not be accepted.
